FBIS4-17208 "drsov078_a_94018" FBIS-SOV-94-078 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS NATO Inspectors Visit Northern Fleet NATO Inspectors Visit Northern Fleet LD2004215094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1347 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004215094 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] In accordance with the treaty on conventional weapons in Europe, a team of U.S., Norwegian and Danish military experts visited the garrisons of Russia's Northern Fleet. Representatives of the department for treaty implementation Captain Aleksandr Arbatov reports that military inspectors have visited the coast-guard division, located in the village of Lesnaya Rechka and the aviation regiment in the village of Katunino in the Arkhangelsk Region, where they were informed of the dislocation of the units and their strength and armaments. This is NATO's third inspection mission to be carried out in the Northern Fleet since the conclusion of the treaty on conventional weapons in Europe and the Vienna document. After the treaty on the reduction of strategic offensive weapons goes into effect, military inspectors will visit the Northern Fleet's nuclear facilities in Severomorsk. The date of the visit has not been fixed yet.
